<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>DevOps Land</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: "Courier New", monospace;
            background-color: #0d1117;
            color: #c9d1d9;
            text-align: center;
            padding-top: 50px;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #58a6ff;
        }
        .ascii {
            font-size: 14px;
            margin-top: 30px;
            color: #8b949e;
        }
        .btn {
            display: inline-block;
            margin: 20px;
            padding: 15px 30px;
            font-size: 16px;
            color: white;
            background-color: #238636;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 8px;
            text-decoration: none;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
            transition: background 0.3s;
        }
        .btn:hover {
            background-color: #2ea043;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Hello from {{ inventory_hostname }} ðŸ‘‹</h1>
    <p>You're now inside a Docker container... inside a VM... inside AWS... running on Terraform... configured with Ansible.</p>
    <p>It's like DevOps Inception around here.</p>

    <div style="margin-top: 40px;">
        <h2>Visit Other Servers</h2>
        {% for server in groups['all'] %}
            <a href="http://{{ hostvars[server]['ansible_host'] }}" class="btn" target="_blank">
                {{ server }}
            </a>
        {% endfor %}
    </div>

    <div class="ascii">
        <pre>
   ,--.
   |oo  |   This is fine.
   |:_/ |   Everything is in a container.
  //   \ \
 (|     | )
/'\_   _/`\
\___)=(___/
        </pre>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
